[SN]TITLE[SN]
Reece Topley: Hampshire left-armer signs new deal until 2018

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Seamer Reece Topley has signed a new deal with county side Hampshire until the end of the 2018 campaign.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 23-year-old left-armer missed almost all of last season after breaking his hand while batting in Hampshire's first Championship match of 2016, before suffering a back injury.
Topley has played 10 one-dayers and six Twenty20 internationals for England.
He has taken 125 first-class wickets at an average of 25.78 since making his debut for Essex in 2011.
